<inglise> COMMISSION DECISION of 27 November 1996 in application, at the request of Germany, of Article 5 (4) of Council Directive 93/75/EEC of 13 September 1993 concerning minimum requirements for vessels bound for or leaving Community ports and carrying dangerous or polluting goods </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI OTSUS n&otilde;ukogu 13. septembri 1993. aasta direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; (miinimumn&otilde;uete kohta, mis k&auml;sitlevad ohtlikke v&otilde;i saastavaid kaupu vedavaid laevu, mis suunduvad &uuml;henduse sadamatesse v&otilde;i lahkuvad sealt) artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaldamisest Saksamaa taotlusel 27. november 1996 </eesti>
<inglise> (The German text alone is authentic) </inglise>
<eesti> (Ainult saksakeelne tekst on autentne) </eesti>
<inglise> (96/710/EC) </inglise>
<eesti> (96/710/E&Uuml;) </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 93/75/EEC of 13 September 1993 concerning minimum requirements for vessels bound for or leaving Community ports and carrying dangerous or polluting goods (1), as amended by Commission Directive 96/39/EC (2), and in particular Article 5 (4) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 13. septembri 1993. aasta direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; miinimumn&otilde;uete kohta, mis k&auml;sitlevad ohtlikke v&otilde;i saastavaid kaupu vedavaid laevu, mis suunduvad &uuml;henduse sadamatesse v&otilde;i lahkuvad sealt, (1) mida on muudetud komisjoni direktiiviga 96/39/E&Uuml;, (2) eriti selle artikli 5 l&otilde;iget 4, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to limit the risks of serious accidents at sea and to reduce the resulting damage, Article 5 of Directive 93/75/EEC provides that the operators of the vessels covered by the Directive shall notify the information listed in Annex I thereto to the competent authorities of the Member State concerned; whereas Article 5 (4) authorizes the Member States to exempt regular scheduled services of less than one hour's crossing time from such notification requirement and allows the Commission to agree to a reasonable extension of this period on request from a Member State; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: v&auml;hendamaks t&otilde;siste &otilde;nnestuste ohtu merel ning sellest tulenevat kahju on direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; artiklis 5 s&auml;testatud, et direktiiviga h&otilde;lmatud laevade kasutajad esitavad selle I lisas loetletud teabe asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele; artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 4 lubatakse liikmesriikidel vabastada sellest teatamisn&otilde;udest alla tunnise &uuml;les&otilde;iduajaga regulaarliinid ning v&otilde;imaldatakse komisjonil n&otilde;ustuda liikmesriigi taotlusel selle aja m&otilde;istliku pikendamisega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, the information given by Germany in its request of 12 April 1994, on the basis of which scheduled services between the mainland and East Frisia Islands were exempted by Decision of the Commission (3) from the application of Article 5 (4) of Directive 93/75/EEC, has been completed by a communication dated 23 February 1996 concerning regular services between the mainland and North Frisia Islands; whereas in this communication, Germany asked the Commission to agree to an exemption for the services operated between the ports of Dageb&uuml;ll to Wittd&uuml;n (Amrum Island) and Schl&uuml;ttsiel to Hallig Langeness, which have crossing times of two hours; </inglise>
<eesti> Saksamaa 12. aprilli 1994. aasta taotluses esitatud teabele, mille alusel mandri ja Ida-Friisi saarte vahelised regulaarliinid vabastati komijoni otsusega (3) direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; artikli 5 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaldamisest, on lisatud 23. veebruari 1996. aasta teatis regulaarliinide kohta mandri ja P&otilde;hja-Friisi saarte vahel; selles teatises palus Saksamaa komisjonil vabastada relulaarliinid Dageb&uuml;lli ja Wittg&uuml;ni (Amrumi saar) ning Sch&uuml;ttsieli ja Hallig Langenessi vahel, mille &uuml;les&otilde;iduajad on 2 tundi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the appropriate measures have been taken by the German competent authorities to ensure a high level of safety of navigation and protection of the marine environment in the area; whereas these measures include traffic surveillance and the provision of safety information to vessels, as well as the obligation to comply with local navigation rules; </inglise>
<eesti> Saksamaa p&auml;devad asutused on v&otilde;tnud kohased meetmed, tagamaks mereliiklusohutuse k&otilde;rge taseme ja merekeskkonna kaitse selles piirkonnas; need meetmed h&otilde;lmavad liiklusj&auml;relevalvet ja laevadele ohutusteabe andmist ning kohustust t&auml;ita kohalikke meres&otilde;idureegleid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the vessels in question provide local services between the islands and the mainland; whereas the risks of accident and marine pollution are limited owing to the scarce maritime traffic in the area and the small quantities of polluting goods on board the vessels; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealused laevad s&otilde;idavad kohalikel liinidel saarte ja mandri vahel; &otilde;nnetuste ja merereostuse oht on v&auml;ike, sest selles piirkonnas ei ole mereliiklus tihe ning laevad veavad saastavaid kaupu v&auml;ikestes kogustes; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the information required by Annex I to the Directive is available at any time from the operators or captains; </inglise>
<eesti> direktiivi I lisas n&otilde;utud teave on kasutajatelt v&otilde;i kaptenitelt igal ajal k&auml;ttesaadav; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in the circumstances, it is justifiable to accept the request from Germany to exempt the regular scheduled services referred to above from the application of Article 5 (2) and (3) of Directive 93/75/EEC, </inglise>
<eesti> antud asjaoludel on n&otilde;ustumine Saksamaa taotlusega vabastada eespool nimetatud regulaarliinid direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; artikli 5 l&otilde;igete 2 ja 3 kohaldamisest p&otilde;hjendatud, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Germany is hereby authorized to exempt the regular scheduled services between Dageb&uuml;ll and Wittd&uuml;n and between Schl&uuml;ttsiel and Hallig Langeness from the application of Article 5 (2) and (3) of Directive 93/75/EEC, subject to the following conditions: </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevaga lubatakse Saksamaal vabastada Dageb&uuml;lli ja Wittg&uuml;ni ning Schl&uuml;ttsieli ja Hallig Langenessi vahelised regulaarliinid direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; artikli 5 l&otilde;igete 2 ja 3 kohaldamisest j&auml;rgmistel tingimustel: </eesti>
<inglise> - the waters in which the services covered by this Decision operate are duly buoyed and are drawn to the attention of navigators in the relevant nautical documents, </inglise>
<eesti> - k&auml;esoleva otsusega h&otilde;lmatud liiklus toimub vetes, mis on kohaselt poidega m&auml;rgistatud ning meres&otilde;itjate t&auml;helepanu juhitakse sellele kohastes meredokumentides, </eesti>
<inglise> - compliance with the local navigation rules is assured, </inglise>
<eesti> - tagatakse kohalike meres&otilde;idureeglite t&auml;itmine, </eesti>
<inglise> - constant contact is maintained, in particular by radio links, with the competent maritime traffic service, </inglise>
<eesti> - p&auml;deva mereliiklustalitusega ollakse pidevas &uuml;henduses, eriti raadioside kaudu, </eesti>
<inglise> - only small quantities of dangerous or polluting goods, within the meaning of Directive 93/75/EEC, are carried on board, </inglise>
<eesti> - laevadel veetakse ohtlikke v&otilde;i saastavaid kaupu ainult v&auml;ikestes kogustes direktiivi 93//5EM&Uuml; t&auml;henduses, </eesti>
<inglise> - the information referred to in Annex I to Directive 93/75/EEC is made available by the operators throughout the crossing and can at any time be provided to the authorities of the Member State on request. </inglise>
<eesti> - direktiivi 93/75/EM&Uuml; I lisas osutatud teave on kasutajatelt k&auml;ttesaadav kogu &uuml;les&otilde;idu jooksul ning taotluse korral saab seda igal ajal esitada liikmesriigi ametiasutustele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the Federal Republic of Germany. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud Saksamaa Liitvabariigile. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 27 November 1996. </inglise>
